Package srg.ship

Class Ship

java.lang.Object
srg.ship.Ship
public class Ship extends Object
Represents a spaceship, which has a unique name, a unique ID, a registered owner, a CargoHold and a NavigationRoom.
Version:
1.2

      public Ship(String name, String owner, String id, RoomTier cargoHoldTier, RoomTier navigationRoomTier, List<SpacePort> galaxyMap)
      Constructs a Ship with a default complement of resources (5x REPAIR_KIT, 100x TRITIUM, 5x HYPERDRIVE_CORE) and specified CargoHold and NavigationRoom quality.
      Parameters:
      name - The ship's name.
      owner - The ship's owner
      id - The ship's id
      cargoHoldTier - The tier of the CargoHold
      navigationRoomTier - The tier of the NavigationRoom
      galaxyMap - The galaxy map to be kept by the NavigationRoom

    • toString

      public String toString()
      Returns a String representation of a Ship. Identifies the name, id, owner, CargoHold and NavigationRoom.
      Overrides:
      toString in class Object
      Returns:
      A String containing details of the Ship. Format must be: "SHIP: name (id) owned by owner\n----\nCargoHold details\nNavigationRoom details".

    • getActions

      public List<String> getActions()
      Get the list of actions that it is possible to perform from this Ship. A Ship is able to perform the actions of its CargoHold and NavigationRoom.
      Returns:
      A List of actions as a string

    • processCommand

      public void processCommand(IO ioHandler, ShipCommand command) throws InsufficientResourcesException, NoPathException, InsufficientCapcaityException
      This method is provided as it interfaces with the command line interface.
      Parameters:
      ioHandler - Handles IO
      command - A command to the ship
      Throws:
      InsufficientResourcesException - If an action cannot be performed due to a lack or resources or a broken Room.
      NoPathException - If a specified SpacePort cannot be found, or cannot be reached.
      InsufficientCapcaityException - If resources cannot be added because there is not enough capacity in the CargoHold.
